The paper describes the development of a predictive model using recurrent neural networks (RNN) to analyze electronic health record (EHR) data. This involves the use of machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the computer science subfields of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on EHR data suggests a potential connection to the subfields of cybernetics (cs.CY) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC), which are concerned with the interaction between humans and technology. Finally, the use of predictive models to analyze medical data may also be relevant to the subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR), which deals with the organization and retrieval of information from large datasets.
